        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-03-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-03-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/3–149: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-04T19:00:00-05:00">March 4, 1949—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>735. Personal for <persName corresp="#p_DLW1">Douglas</persName>. Fol message
                    from <persName corresp="#p_HP1">Hoffman</persName> sent at his request.</p>
                <p>Ref Emtel 773.<note n="1" xml:id="d275fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> I am greatly concerned present Brit
                    position that prohibited and restricted industries and reparations issues must
                    be settled together. I believe it of utmost importance that Brit and Fr be
                    advised strong efforts now being made in Congress which have thus far been
                    resisted to introduce legislation which could blow up entire reparation issue
                    and result in final US position which goes far beyond <persName corresp="#p_HGA1">Humphrey</persName> Report<note n="2" xml:id="d275fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> in plant retention and would result in cut in funds
                    allocated countries receiving reparations equipment. Success of resistance this
                    or similar legislation cannot be guaranteed. In any event as indicated earlier
                    there will be considerable and heated debate this issue and <persName corresp="#p_HGA1">Humphrey</persName> Report will probably be public domain
                    before issue resolved.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
